We will create a simple application that allows to store information on books

1. Install compoundjs
sudo npm install compound -g

After that compound command appears for you, so you can start working with compound

2. You can see commands of compound
compound command

3. create new "library" application
compound init "library"

4. see structure of folders in "library" application
tmp/library
tree

5. open the following file and do appropriate modification to modify db and env settings (optional)
database.json - you can set your db there 
environment.js - set your environment variables

6. install all necessary dependencies
npm install -l

7. you can now generate new entities
compound generate crud books title content author

8. make server listen
compound server 8888

9. see your application
open http://127.0.0.1:8888/posts
